<h2 align="center" style="text-align:center">PMP&reg; Certification Exam Application Process</h2>
                	  <p>The<strong> Project Management Professional </strong>PMP&reg; program is under the control and jurisdiction of the Project Management Institute(PMI) organization. Perspective should follow this process in order to apply for the <strong>PMI-PMP</strong> certification</p>
<ol class="style1">
                	    <li class="">Register as a member of the Project Management Institute at <a href="http://www.pmi.org/" target="_blank">www.pmi.org</a>. We recommend registering for both the basic membership as well as your local chapter. The Exam cost for members is $405.00, compared to $555.00 for non-members.</li>
              	        <li class="">Complete the Online Project Management Professional PMP&reg; Application.</li>
           	          </ol>
                	  <ul class="">
                	    <li> You will need to document <strong>4,500 hours</strong> (with a 4 yr degree) to<strong> 7,500 hours</strong> (w/o degree) of experience in the Project Management Body of Knowledge domains, equal to approximately 2 1/4 to 4 years non-overlapping experience. </li>
              	        <li>A training certificate of at least <strong>35 contact hours</strong> of Project Management training (PDU's) is required to register for the exam. If you don't have the necessary hours our PMP&reg; Certification Exam Prep course will satisfy that requirement. We also have a pre-course self study module that provides you with the required PDU's before class, if you have the time.</li>
                	    <li>PMI may conduct reference checks as part of the periodic audit process. If you are audited, you will be notified via email.</li>
                	  </ul>
                	  <blockquote class="style4">                	    
                	    <p class="">Once you have received approval, you should schedule your <strong>PMP&reg; Certification Exam.</strong> You should try   															  and schedule the test within 5 days after class. You can do this online at <a href="http://www.prometric.com/PMI/default.htm" target="_blank"> Prometric.</a></p>
                	    <p class="">Now, you are ready to attend the Pinnacle 3 Learning <a href="pmp-certification-training.aspx"><strong>PMP&reg; Certification Exam Prep Course</strong></a> and PASS the exam <strong>Project Management Professional</strong> (PMP&reg; )Certification Examination!</p>
                	  </blockquote>                	  
